<Content>Good value, great location. My friends and I stayed at the Hotel Catedral for four nights in October 2008. The hotel is nice and clean. Beds were firmer than I prefer, but typical for Mexico. 95% of the front desk staff were very friendly and there was nearly always someone there who spoke English. The Hotel Catedral was within easy walking distance of all of the Centro Historico sites: Palacio Nacional, Catedral Municipal, Palacio de Bellas Artes, Zocalo, Temple Mayor, etc. The Cathedral and National Palace were visible from my room. The rooftop gardens were great for watching sunrises and just getting away from the street noise.We had breakfast and lunch at the hotel a couple of times and all of the meals were very good. The service was also fine at the hotel restaurant.Hotel staff were good about calling cabs when we needed them, but we found that the cab drivers generally charged more than the hotel staff quoted.The only negative was our check in. We arrived at the hotel at 11 pm, many hours later than expected after flight delays in the U.S. Their was only one attendant at the front desk that night and he seemed preoccupied with talking with someone on the phone. He may have been taking reservations, but it was hard to tell. He spoke English (and I speak some spanish) but he made no effort to indicate that he would be right with us. Anyway, it took about 40 minutes to actually get the keys to our rooms. Also, he tried to put us in rooms different from what we reserved. He wouldn't consider changing our rooms until we showed him a print out of our reservation. Again, all the other front desk staff, bellmen, etc. were very nice, friendly and professional. 
