<Author>Ravennarose96
<Content>One more "Ole" for Catedral My wife and I just got back from a 4 night stay in Hotel Catedral. Both it and Mexico City make for a perfect getaway. We had a decent-sized and spotless double room for what worked out to be about $51 US per night. (We paid in cash, and the peso is a little stronger lately.) Bathroom clean and modern with plenty of hot water and water pressure. Staff friendly and efficient, and the restaurant very good, though we only ate breakfast there each day. We booked the tour to Teotihuacan at the lobby tour desk, which took less than a minute and cost $25 apiece. I think other reviwers had issues with this, but we thought it was flawless with a mature and intelligent guide taking us around a unique and fascinating site.Mexico City itself was a pleasant surprise. Every street we wandered around Centro and Coyoacan was litter free, and we felt safe any moment of the day or night, possibly attributable to the police presence wherever we turned. The citizens were polite, and, as with everywhere we've been in Mexico, the children remarkably well-behaved. Also, I can't think of a reason in the world to take a taxi except for to/from airport (about $12 US) because the metro is so extensive, clean, fast and absurdly cheap. Finally, we won't recommend specific restaurants because tastes differ, but we found it impossible to get a bad meal even from the humblest cantina or one that could be considered pricey when we went upscale.The only reason we don't give the hotel 5 stars is because, well, it's just not a 5 star hotel. But we travel a lot, and we're hard-pressed to think of another stopover that gives the same value for money. 
