<Author>priscilla
<Content>Good location and value On our way home from a two month stay in Buenos Aires we spent a week in Mexico City. We really enjoyed our stay at the Hotel Catedral. It was a nice hotel and very close to the 'action'. It was also a great value. The city was interesting, but it just so happened we were there during 'Holy week' and it was an absolute 'MOB SCENE'!! The sidewalks were so crowded, walking was a challenge. We were also very disappointed since we were unable to see some of the local attractions because the lines to get in were blocks and hours long.We had made reservations about 6 months before our trip and then reconfirmed them a few days before we left Buenos Aires. When we arrived at the hotel they had no reservation for us!! That was not good news since we had just gotten off a plane after a 9+ hour flight. They did put is in an upgraded room for one night and the next morning we moved to a regular double room. It was a bit of a hassle, but at least we had a place to sleep. We chose to do the breakfast package (about an extra $115 pesos for two) and we had a nice selection of breakfast items. We later realized after we studied the menu that it really cost more than if we had just ordered off the regular menu so beware! We could have had a few more choices and and saved a few dollars too.In one of the previous reviews someone had mentioned the construction next door. That was a problem for us too and we had to change rooms because the workmen where outside almost all night long. Just make sure you ask for a room far from the construction noise.The hotel is all non-smoking which is a big plus! The lovely rooftop terraces were nice, but that is where smoking is allowed. Be prepared to have your nice view sullied by cigarette smoke. It would be nice if one of the terraces would also be non-smoking.Overall the Hotel Catedral is a great value and I would recommend it to anyone who wants a good location and value. 
