<Content>Great hotel. Brutal tour We stayed at Hotel Catedral for 1 week in late November. The staff was friendly and very helpful. The rooftop patio was a nice place to wind down at the end of the day with litre bottles of sol from the 7 11 on the corner (16 pesos per liter). The bar behind the hotel was noisy thursday to saturday but we were not expecting peace and quiet in the center of Mexico City anyway so it wasnt a big deal. The beds were really hard but after a full day of walking around we fell asleep easily. All in all the hotel met and exceeded our expectations it is in a prime location and the price was right.The tour on the other hand was a nightmare. We had taken the same tour from Roldan travel 2 years ago on a previous trip to the city. That one was great, very informative and interesting. Therefore we had high expectations for this one as well. We had friends travel with us and told them how great the pyramids would be and how much fun they would have. Wrong. We met our guide at the Cathedral of Guadalupe as we were joining a tour already in progress. We waited for 15 minutes for a inconsiderate lady who was more interested in shopping than going to the pyramids. She is a whole different story I wont get into that it is still too fresh lol. On the way to the pyramids we stopped at a obsidian art factory. Had a tour of the facility and were then rushed into the store to have the chance to spend thousands of dollars on masks and figurines. No thanks. Where are the pyramids? After the tourist trap we arrived finally at the pyramids. To truly appreciate where you are you need to spend at least 3 hours. We had 45 minutes (inconsiderate shopper strikes again at the mask factory).After an uninformative tour compared to our last tour experience we were brought to the International restaurant for lunch. We were told the house specialty was great so we decided to try it. 150 pesos but good food. We were asked if we like guacamole to wich we answered yes. We were brought a little bowl of guacamole, 4 chips and 4 pork rinds. When we got the bill we found out they charged us 100 pesos for 1 peso worth of guacamole. So instead of spending 1 hour more at the pyramids we were brought to a tourist trap and hosed on guacamole. Not a happy tour van after that. So dont use Roldan tours. Try someone in the Zocalo and whatever you do dont order the guacamole. Made my wife ill at the end of the day. 
