<Content>Fantastic location, best value, great for kids Having read through many tripadvisor reviews, my husband and I decided on the Hotel Catedral as the place to stay for 8 nights (June 5-13) during our vacation with our two young daughters. We were not disappointed. Our double bed room was quite comfortable with space for a crib at $518 MXN ($50 CDN) a night incl taxes, when paid in cash or traveller's cheques. Very clean and well-kept, with purified water from a separate tap. The room was just as it appears on the website. Our bathroom was spacious with a tiled shower stall. With our room being on the 4th floor next to the inner courtyard, we had no problems with noise whatsoever. We enjoyed a wide selection of breakfast meals each day at the hotel restaurant. They have high chairs and TVs to watch FIFA World Cup. Very friendly and prompt service every time. The internet connection was $10 pesos for 15 min, and was quick and reliable. The hotel staff were always there to open doors, carry luggage, help the girls up the front stairs--excellent service, indeed!But above all the favorable features I listed, you cannot beat the location. We thought of staying near the Zona Rosa, but were so happy to have chosen the Historic Center instead. The Z贸calo and historic sites are just around the corner from the hotel, which alone is worth a few days of sightseeing (at least!). There are many specialized local shops in the immediate area, and the Dept stores Liverpool and El Palacio de Hierro are a 5 min walk away. Fantastic restaurants all within a few blocks--do not miss the Hoster铆a de Santo Domingo. The Metro is so handy and easy to use, only a few minutes walk through the Z贸calo crowds, and the Turibus stop is even closer. Note that the Turibus does not operate on Mondays, as most museums and sites are closed. It was a breathtaking sight each evening as we walked through the Z贸calo to get back to the hotel. We did not feel unsafe at all, but then again did not venture out past 9 PM.To see the pyramids and Basilica, we hired a private taxi through the hotel for the day at $700 pesos and had no problems at all. The taxi to the airport took only 25 min (8 AM on a Tuesday for $100 pesos). Overall, we loved our stay in Mexico City and would definitely recommend this hotel. 
