<Content>Fantastic Find You may be put off when you arrive to this Hotel at 2 a.m. from the airport. The downtown is a drab place at that time, with hookers on every corner. Fortunately there is the Hotel catedral, a safe, clean place, with someone at the desk 24/7. The Hotel is excellently located, the downtown area improves greately during the day and in the evening. We never felt unsafe in Mexico City. As a bonus, the Hotel is located right on the edge of what might be world's largest street market, where all streets east, north east and south east turn into a huge daily market. Weekends are bussiest.We found the hotel to be quiet, clean and safe, with staff being pleasant and helpful.Heavy and dark window shades kept the room cool. There was purified water tap in the bathroom.Some rooms have bathtubs, most have showers, so look around and choose what you like.We really appreciated the roof patio. The downtown Mexico offer very few places to sit down and relax, so it was nice to be able to come home and take a breath outside. Sipping beer at night on the patio was great too. Patio is on the 7th floor.Rooms on the 7th floor are hottest, being the highest, so if you want to be close to the patio, go for the 6th floor.Night taxi ride from the airport took 15 minutes, and going back to the airport at 6.30 p.m. took 25 minutes. The hotel arranged a taxi, although it was a private car, not an official taxi, at a cost of 120 pesos ($11). 
