<Author>ampy
<Content>Thanks to all who recommended Hotel Catedral We just returned from Mexico City...Nov 24 to Nov 27...we took the advice of many trip advisors and stayed in Hotel Catedral at the Zocalo...we are very grateful ..my husband, 30 year old son and I were given a nice clean room with 2 double beds..we paid $ 48 a day, a real bargain, for the 3 of us...the hotel is walking distance to many points of interest in the Zocalo...although some trip advisors wrote that it was noisy at night, it was quiet in our side of the hotel and we slept very soundly...staff was courteous and helpful...TV was colored and had 2 or 3 English channels...no aircon, only ceiling fan but temperature was okay in late November..bathroom was clean with big bath towels, soap and shampoo..there was a faucet with purified water, safe for brushing teeth.... 2 REMINDERS: please bring your own hand and face towels, also, put the bath towels on the floor or the sink so that the cleaning woman will giveyou fresh towels the next day...free safe deposit box where we kept our passports, tickets and money...nice, cheap restaurant downstairs....plenty of hangers in the closet...we brought our own bottles of water to drink...but they have very good orange,grapefruit, papaya, and carrot juices, cheap too....the coffee was too strong for us....we paid 175 pesos for taxi from the airport to the hotel and 100 pesos from the hotel back to the airport..please do not get the tours from the hotel, they are expensive...instead walk about 2 short blocks to the hostel on the Zocalo to get the cheap tours there...the best way to travel is by metro, 2 pesos, fast , but please be very careful with your wallets....we went by metro to the Shrine of Our Lady of Guadalupe, 3 transfers to the northern section of Mexico City...taxis and buses are slower because of the traffic....remember to take the red double decker bus that will take you on a tour around the city for 3 hours, 100 pesos, worth it. we rode on the top and enjoyed it...we ate at the rooftop of Majestic Hotel close by and found the view of the Zocalo very nice from the terrace...but we were so disappointed with the food at Majestic, bad, soggy, and poorly presented ( dinner ) and expensive...food was better at the Hotel Catedral....we recommend Mexican Viejo Restaurant, about 1 block from the Square...brunch was buffet, eat all you can for 65 pesos, a real steal....we enjoyed shopping at the square but we haggled, about less than half their quoted price...I bought a lot of good stuff for Christmas gifts...again, please take care that you check the items you purchase for damages...we were extra careful not to buy food from sidewalk vendors ...we brought face masks ( for pollution ) and imodium ( for diarrhea) but did not use them, thank God....Trip Advisor, thank you for making our trip to Mexico City an affair to remember.......... 
