<Author>dbltrbl05
<Content>recommend it highly! we stayed at hotel catedral for three nights, nov. 1 - 3/04. it had been recommended by friends, and we were extremely happy there. as many others before me have commented, this place is a steal, as well as being the real deal. service at the front desk is courteous and helpful. we were in room 512, and used the stairs every day. one note - what they call the 5th floor is actually the 6th floor, as what they call the 1st floor is what we would call the 2nd!here are a few random observations -- we ate at the hotel restaurant several times. breakfasts were pretty good, but beware that sausages are actually wieners. you might be better off asking for ham or bacon, with your eggs. one night we wanted just grilled fish, vegetables and rice. we asked if they could prepare that for us, and they did. it was delicious...about $10US each. we laughed about how they charged for bread. they always put bread on the table, and would sometimes charge us, whether we had any or not. we couldnt figure it out, but it was no biggie, so we didnt call them on it.one morning, at breakfast, i put my purse on the floor beside my chair. the server immediately brought me a small stand, like a coat stand, and hung my purse on it. he explained that it is bad luck to put purses or knapsacks on the floor. the funny thing is that he could have put it on one of the spare chairs, since there were two spare chairs at our table.- the taxi cost 175 pesos from the airport to the hotel, but only 100 from the hotel to the airport- thx to those who recommended the red double decker bus tour! we thoroughly enjoyed it. as mentioned, it is a three-hour tour, with hop on and off privileges. we made it last the entire day. we made only one long stop, however, at chapultepec park. we loved it! we visited the zoo, the museum of anthropology and the castle. all must-sees. - the only english station on TV is CNN. it came in handy for watching the US presidential election on nov. 2.- i always take extra hangers cause i like to hang most of my clothing. there were more hangers than i have ever seen at a hotel, anywhere!- there is a tap in the bathroom (to the right of the sink) that provides purified water. i didnt chance it. i drank only bottled water, but im sure its safe.and now for a little anecdote. i have to admit i was a bit worried about safety in mexico city. that said, we felt very safe whenever we went outside, although we werent out extremely late at night. we rode the subway, which was efficient and fairly easy to navigate. what i want to share with you was what happened on our first evening out...this was the conversation between my husband and me -me: walk behind me, in case i get mugged.him: what if i get mugged?me: better you than me!hehein summary, thx to everyone for the reviews and tips. if we return to mexico city, and we hope to at some point, we will definitely stay at hotel catedral. we would give it our highest recommendation! have a great stay, and feel free to email me if you have any questions. 
