<Content>Great location, but... We stayed at the Hotel Catedral for a total of three nights on two separate occasions in March, 2004. While the room was large and well-appointed, it was almost uncomfortably warm, despite rather cool outside temperatures. In addition, despite it's great location only blocks from the Zocalo and the Templo Mayor, it took us a bit of time to get from the hotel to either the airport or the Terminal Norte bus station, especially during rush hour. If you're looking for a place to stay that's more convenient to either the airport or the bus terminal, you might want to look elsewhere. If you want a place that's more centrally located, though, I'd recommend the Hotel Catedral highly. The restaurant food is both good and reasonably priced (although it doesn't open until 8am and is as brightly lit as a Morton's Cafeteria), the Junior Suites with 2-person Jacuzzi are a bargain at around $50, and the service is quite good. 
