<Author>crazycycler
<Content>Great Service at the Catedral On a recommendation from a Travel Advisor reader we stayed at the Hotel Catedral near the Zocala in Mexico City. The staff were outstanding from a service perspective and the rooms were clean and well maintained. On Sunday morning we had to be at the airport at 0530 hours to catch a flight home. The hotel called a taxi for us and we arrived safely at the airport. After checking in, however, my husband discovered he had lost his wallet. With help from an Mexico City resident, we called the hotel and asked them if they could track down the taxi we had used to see if the driver had found the wallet. While we waited on the phone, they called the driver and indeed he had my husband's wallet. The hotel asked him to bring it to us at the airport, which he did. Nothing was missing from the wallet which the driver had carefully tucked in his pocket. I can't say enough positive things about the hotel staff. I highly recommend the Hotel Catedral for visitors to Mexico City. 
