<Author>stevecaron
<Content>Spotless, Great Value My wife and I stayed here on 2 separate occasions in Feb 2004. In both cases we selected a Junior Suite (540 pesos all taxes in). Both suites were absolutely spotless and everything worked well in the suite i.e. toilet, shower, jacuzzi etc. The area is a little 'downmarket' compared to the Polanco and Zona Rosa areas but it is centrally located and the Hotel value is tremendous. We also ate breakfasts in the Hotel's restaurant and found the food and prices to be very good - certainly a cut above most hotel food - and the service to be excellent. For an overview of the city we highly recommend taking the red double decker tour buses that leave every 30 minutes from in front of the Catedral on the Zocalo. It costs 100 pesos (110 on weekends) but gives you a 3 hour tour of the City with hop-on hop-off privileges - with our hop-offs we stretched the trip from 9 AM until 6 PM. Enjoy your trip ! 
