<Content>Value Galore, I Need Not Say More! Spent three nights here the third week in January 2004 on part of a 7 night tour of various colonial cities. By far and away the best value and our favorite hotel of the stay. Conveniently located near the National Cathedral (duh I think that is where they got the name) the Zocalo, Metro (subway) station, Girabaldi Plaza (marriachi central) markets, and Alameda park and Palacio de Las Bellas Artes if you can walk a little. True they did not have shoe polish (we were wearing sneakers) shower caps (I'm hair challenged) hand lotion and other small items like hand towels (but the three bath towels were plenty big) but they did not have a high price either. I felt safe night and day (tons of people in the day time and quite a few at night time) were found on the streets. Internet access cost 10 pesos per 15 minutes (business hotel in Queretaro the night before was 80 pesos for half an hour.) The cost was reasonable and kept it so no one stayed on forever so access was available. Clean, safe, inexpensive - I loved it. 
